title: [CRASH]
body:
**Crash report**

Paste the complete crash log between the quotes below. Please include a few lines from the log preceding the crash report to provide some context.

```
------ MODULES INFO OUTPUT ------
# graph_executing commands
graph_command:GRAPH.QUERY MATCH (n) DETACH DELETE n;

------ FAST MEMORY TEST ------
1:M 13 Feb 2022 15:55:01.066 # main thread terminated
1:M 13 Feb 2022 15:55:01.066 # Bio thread for job type #0 terminated
1:M 13 Feb 2022 15:55:01.067 # Bio thread for job type #1 terminated
1:M 13 Feb 2022 15:55:01.067 # Bio thread for job type #2 terminated

Fast memory test PASSED, however your memory can still be broken. Please run a memory test for several hours if possible.

------ DUMPING CODE AROUND EIP ------
Symbol: GB_setElement (base: 0x4003745ea0)
Module: /usr/lib/redis/modules/redisgraph.so (base 0x4003555000)
$ xxd -r -p /tmp/dump.hex /tmp/dump.bin
$ objdump --adjust-vma=0x4003745ea0 -D -b binary -m i386:x86-64 /tmp/dump.bin
------
1:M 13 Feb 2022 15:55:01.069 # dump of function (hexdump of 990 bytes):

Function at 0x40037308c0 is GB_code_compatible
Function at 0x4003841800 is GB_code_type
Function at 0x4003764e90 is GB_wait
Function at 0x40037308f0 is GB_code_string

=== REDIS BUG REPORT END. Make sure to include from START to END. ===

       Please report the crash by opening an issue on github:

           http://github.com/redis/redis/issues

  Suspect RAM error? Use redis-server --test-memory to verify it.

qemu: uncaught target signal 11 (Segmentation fault) - core dumped
```

**Additional information**

1. OS distribution and version

Macbook 2021 M1 Pro Max
MacOS Monterey 12.1 (21C52
Running docker run -p 6379:6379 -it --rm redislabs/redisgraph

2. Steps to reproduce (if any)

- docker run -p 6379:6379 -it --rm redislabs/redisgraph
- Open RedisInsight
- Run `GRAPH.QUERY "graph" "MATCH (n) DETACH DELETE n;"`
